CommandDoccommentNode.comment: A functional queue data structure, using two back-to-back lists. If we think of the queue as having elements pushed on the front and popped from the back, then the queue itself is effectively `eList ++ dList.reverse`. -/

CommandDoccommentNode.comment: The enqueue list, which stores elements that have just been pushed (with the most recently enqueued elements at the head). -/

CommandDoccommentNode.comment: The dequeue list, which buffers elements ready to be dequeued (with the head being the next item to be yielded by `dequeue?`). -/

CommandDoccommentNode.comment: `O(|vs|)`. Push a list of elements `vs` on the front of the queue. -/

CommandDoccommentNode.comment: `O(1)` amortized, `O(n)` worst case. Pop an element from the back of the queue, returning the element and the new queue. -/

CommandDoccommentNode.comment: `O(n)`. Applies the monadic predicate `p` to every element in the queue, and returns the queue of elements for which `p` returns `true`. Note that there are currently no guarantees for the order that `p` is applied in. -/
